<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4536192>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 4. — Stephanollina dentata Vigneaux, 1949, figured syntype C.B.429-1, Langhian, middle Miocene, Manciet, Gers, Aquitaine, France: A, general view of the colony; the arrow shows an autozooid with developed suboral mucro; B, group of zooids with incomplete ovicells and broken avicularian chambers; C, close-up of two autozooids with elliptical avicularia; D, close-up of the primary orifice showing five oral spine bases and the cormidial secondary orifice with alternating lobes and cusps. Scale bars: A, 200 μm; B, 100 μm; C, D, 50 μm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4536192/files/figure.png" .

